Children born ol a connection which was not a legal marriage, either because it was prohibited by some positive rule, or because there was no maritalis affectio, were deemed, as a rule, to have no father: ‘vulgo concepti dicuntur, qui patrem demonstrare non possunt, vel qui possunt quidem, sed eum habent quern habere non licet, qui et spurii appellantur παρὰ τὴν σποράν’ Dig. 1. 5. 23.
